refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
resourcefalsefbsql_list_dbs resourcelink_identifier
Return a result pointer containing the databases available from the current fbsql daemon. Use the fbsql_tablename to traverse this result pointer.

  &reftitle.examples;



    fbsql_list_dbs example


<?php
$link = fbsql_connect('localhost', 'myname', 'secret');
$db_list = fbsql_list_dbs($link);

while ($row = fbsql_fetch_object($db_list)) {
    echo $row->Database . "\n";
}
?>


    &example.outputs.similar;


database1
database2
database3
...







    The above code would just as easily work with
    fbsql_fetch_row or other similar functions.
